@AndreasGassmann we would rather discuss that in a separate issue. But one thing: the error message is an attempt to communicate that we do not really want to support using "requireCordovaModule" to load non-Cordova module "q" any longer. We really recommend that you consider importing and requiring the `q` module in your own code, as we tried to indicate in the warning message. Our time to support old functionality is extremely limited.

@videmort this is an expected change. 

Plugins should not be using modules that Cordova uses internally. We have also been removing Q from our libraries tools and platforms etc.

If a plugin relies on the `Q` npm package, that plugin should be updated to include this package as a dependency and use the native `require` call.

@brainssolutions The `res` folder is not special in any way. You can also name the folder `resources` as you have to specify the paths to the icons in your `config.xml` anyway.

That being said, the _double_ double quoted attributes in your XML snippet look dubious.
Another thing to watch out for: Those paths are relative to the project root, not the `www` folder.

